The paper discusses the use of bidirectional learning for improving the robustness of neural networks, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces novel techniques for improving robustness to adversarial examples, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the issue of white noise static, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CR.
